All the feels today at the @puntagordayouthbaseball Opening Day kick off! 

Team Angels had a double header- won both games and played great! 

Gage played 1st base and took home the game ball for the 1st game. He was beyond stoked. Then he got his 1st infield homer in in the 2nd game, wooooo!!! 

I was so happy to help as Team Mom in the dugout. The kiddos are awesome and I’m grateful for the opportunity to be involved. 

Lastly, we raffled off a @fishtenacity offshore trip to help raise $ for the league. Awesome seeing all the folks involved in the program coaching and volunteering their time, and all the kiddos out there working hard and having fun!

A little throwback bcuz it’s March and it always reminds me of the MadFin SharkSeries days. @captbojohnson and I had quite the run. Competed/ filmed 4 years.. 1st guy-girl team to win.. won it 2x. Had an absolute blast with cast and crew. Prob one of my fav accomplishments and experiences of all times. And amazing I was able to do it with my man 🖤. He taught me everything I know when it comes to shark wrangling and then some. Grateful for the great outdoors and this crazy life!!

Doesn’t get much better than this!! Shotgun shopping with pops at my childhood Cabelas in KC, MO. Soooo weird seeing it as BPS now. I’ll always hear daddy’s voice sayn Cabelas 😊 The nostalgia was ripe with memories - one in particular where I won a duck calling contest and brought daddy home a blacked out Benelli SuperNova pump action. Not long after, he handed me down a Beretta 391 Urika 12 gauge semi auto that would be with me the next 20 years!Ducks, quail, pheasant, Turkey and clays. She put in her time. Looking to update/ diversify, I’m excited to have finally pulled the trigger on 2yrs of research and having my dad there to talk it all through was worth the wait!  #BerettaA400SportingXcelBlack #12gauge #SemiAutoShotgun #SportingClays #TheGreatOutdoors #ChildhoodNostalgia @bassproshops @cabelas @beretta_usa

Our annual hunting vacay has had quite the outcome! 

Gage definitely came out as the champion with harvesting his first ever deer (a doe), then his first buck, a few does to help fulfill TX ranch herd management, and then a massive cherry on top— an axis buck!!! (I am not jealous, I am not jealous… 🤐😄). He took all with his new gun, but we are super proud of his practicing with the crossbow and compound bow. And happy not happy with all the taxidermy bills he stacked up 😅

Bo scored an absolute beauty of a Missouri archery buck (and now has the biggest buck in the house replacing my record 😩 I mean 😃 lol), then a nice Texas ten point with gun, and a few does to help with the herd mgmt goals.. And he hunted with Gage so mama could sleep in and hunt afternoons 🤷🏻‍♀️

Then there’s me. I tell ya what.. if more women recognized the absolute bliss that comes from sitting in a stand by yourself in peace and quiet, they would hunt! Of course I am motivated with putting organic delicious food on my family’s table - okay okay and I’m sporty/ competitive - so it’s just the perfect combo for this mama. Being I only hunt afternoons and had 6 days to toy with.. I got my Texas archery buck (2nd biggest to date!) early on .. and then went shopping 🛍️🙌, woop! Honestly with all the drive and success my men were having, this trip was already a huge victory. I’d say the only goal that evaded me was an axis doe. Man I wanted that meat and to make a rug outa their exquisite cape. We did some spot n stalks and some drives but didn’t pan out. That’ll be top the list for next year. 

Grateful for our family hunting tradition - the experiences garnered and memories made and shared with our amazing friends @micah.mckinney @kathleenkennedy77. Grateful for the nourishment this wild, organic meat provides and the lessons learned that only comes from our great outdoors!
